tool.name: TerrengkriterierTool
tool.displayname: Compute slope with respect to sourcepoints

param.name: lines
param.dialogReference: Polyline or Point features to be used as source for computing the terrain criteria. Attribute table MUST have a field named "ewd" for the estimated water depth/depth of landslide initiation. If it is a point feature it must additionally come with a field named RASTERVALU with the elevation of the points (result from ExtractValuesToPoints). If source points come from Drainage and Source Points toolbox, then the format is already compliant.

param.name: in_raster
param.dialogReference: Input Digital Elevation Model. The computation will cover the whole extent of the DEM. It is recommended to clip the raster to the desired extent before running the toolbox.

param.name: out_raster
param.dialogReference: Raster with the results as vertical:horizontal-ratio computed in relation to the source points.

param.name: delta
param.dialogReference: Chainage distance. The source lines will be divided into points at the specified distance.

param.name: h_min
param.dialogReference: Minimum slope height. It is set to 5 m according to NVE 1/2019.

tool.summary:
This ArcGIS Pro toolbox calculates terrain slopes in relation to "source points" (points from where a landslide can initiate) to verify wheter the terrain fullfills the criteria established by NVE for defining quick clay landslide hazard zones (NVE 1/2019 Kvikkleireveileder).

It allows users to quickly and accurately assess potential risk areas, helping them make informed decisions about land use and development in affected areas.

Ref: https://publikasjoner.nve.no/veileder/2019/veileder2019_01.pdf
